    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Mounting Engine on Engine Stand -
        Removal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT)</title>
            <figure id="f3350002052" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figK09/K09043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>VGT actuator connector and turbocharger air intake duct</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger air intake duct</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Breather tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Lock tab (up to unlock)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Release tab (push to release)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT actuator</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen worm gear clamps on the turbocharger air intake duct and breather tube. Pull
                    turbocharger air intake duct assembly off the VGT and crankcase breather.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push lock tab up to unlock VGT actuator connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press the release tab and pull sensor harness connector out of the VGT actuator
                    connector.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350002053" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk15/K15001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger oil supply tube assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger oil supply tube nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 25 bolt (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger oil supply tube nut from the fitting on top of the oil filter
                    header.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two M8 x 25 bolts connecting the turbocharger oil supply tube assembly to the VGT
                    oil supply port and remove the tube assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350002054" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk15/K15002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>VGT oil drain tube, bracket, and bolt</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 16 bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil drain tube bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil drain tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove M8 x 16 bolt from VGT oil drain tube bracket and remove bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull oil drain tube out of crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350002055" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk15/K15003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>VGT mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 VGT mounting nut (4)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger mounting gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT mounting stud</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To aid removal of the turbocharger, loosen four M10 nuts &#188; turn then tap each nut using a
                        socket or flat punch and hammer. This will knock the "peaks" of the threads down, allowing the
                        nuts to unthread easily.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, support the turbocharger assembly during removal and
                        installation.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three of four M10 mounting nuts holding the VGT assembly to the exhaust
                    manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the VGT assembly and remove the fourth M10 nut holding the VGT to the exhaust
                    manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the VGT assembly and oil drain tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap openings on turbocharger assembly. If plastic caps are not available, use duct tape
                    to cover openings.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
